The paper deals with object detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm is a machine learning technique, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
